<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2137">
You are given an $n \times n$ grid whose each square is either black or white. A subgrid is called <i>beautiful</i> if its height and width is at least two and all of its corners are black. How many beautiful subgrids are there within the given grid?<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has an integer $n$: the size of the grid.<br />
<br />
Then there are $n$ lines describing the grid: <code>1</code> means that a square is black and <code>0</code> means it is white.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print the number of beautiful subgrids.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 3000$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>5<br />
00010<br />
11111<br />
00110<br />
11001<br />
00010<br />
</code><br />
Output:<br />
<code>4</code>    </div>
